## Chile at the 2015 Pan American Games

Chile, under the [IOC code](/List_of_IOC_country_codes) CHI, sent a delegation of 306 athletes to compete in the [2015 Pan American Games](/2015_Pan_American_Games). These Games were held in [Toronto](/Toronto), [Ontario](/Ontario), Canada, from July 10 to 26, 2015. The [National Olympic Committee](/National_Olympic_Committee) responsible for this delegation was the Comité Olímpico de Chile. The nation participated across 34 distinct sports, a testament to the breadth of athletic talent and dedication within Chile. The [flagbearer](/2015_Pan_American_Games_national_flag_bearers) for the opening ceremony was the track and field athlete [Isidora Jiménez](/Isidora_Jim%C3%A9nez), a choice made through a public vote. For the closing ceremony, the honor of [flagbearer](/2015_Pan_American_Games_closing_ceremony) fell to [Erika Olivera](/Erika_Olivera). Chile's performance at these Games resulted in a total of 29 medals, securing them the 11th position in the overall [medals table](/2015_Pan_American_Games_medal_table). This haul consisted of 5 gold, 6 silver, and 18 bronze medals.

Chile has a long-standing tradition of participation in the Pan American Games, with their presence dating back to the inaugural event in [1951](/Chile_at_the_1951_Pan_American_Games). Their consistent involvement includes appearances in [1955](/Chile_at_the_1955_Pan_American_Games), [1959](/Chile_at_the_1959_Pan_American_Games), [1963](/Chile_at_the_1963_Pan_American_Games), [1967](/Chile_at_the_1967_Pan_American_Games), [1971](/Chile_at_the_1971_Pan_American_Games), [1975](/Chile_at_the_1975_Pan_American_Games), [1979](/Chile_at_the_1979_Pan_American_Games), [1983](/Chile_at_the_1983_Pan_American_Games), [1987](/Chile_at_the_1987_Pan_American_Games), [1991](/Chile_at_the_1991_Pan_American_Games), [1995](/Chile_at_the_1995_Pan_American_Games), [1999](/Chile_at_the_1999_Pan_American_Games), [2003](/Chile_at_the_2003_Pan_American_Games), [2007](/Chile_at_the_2007_Pan_American_Games), [2011](/Chile_at_the_2011_Pan_American_Games), and most recently in [2019](/Chile_at_the_2019_Pan_American_Games) and [2023](/Chile_at_the_2023_Pan_American_Games), in addition to the 2015 Games. An overview of Chile's participation in the Pan American Games can be found [here](/Chile_at_the_Pan_American_Games).

